Jul 1 2004	Best deal in one of the nicest areas	We stayed at the london house for 10 days. When we arrived we discovered it was in a nice and safe neighborhood with many similar hotels in the area. The nearest tube stop was either paddington or lancaster gate, both a 5 minute walk away, there were also many grocery and 24hr conveniance stores on craven hill along with a place that sells a full english breakfast for 2.50GBP which is dirt cheap by british prices. Our room was a triple with one queen bed and one twin, there was also a small dining table, microwave, fridge, dishes, tv, airconditioner, and a nice clean bathroom. we paid 47GBP a night which is very cheap for a triple anywhere in london let alone Bayswater. We found our rate online, the advertised price when we arrived was 115GBP per nite for a triple so we got an especially good deal.	
